[size=16pt][b][color=#ffaa00]⚠️ Why It Matters[/color][/b][/size]

[b][color=#ff0000]Harvest-Now-Decrypt-Later:[/color][/b] Adversaries are [b]already recording[/b] encrypted blockchain traffic. When quantum computers arrive, they'll decrypt historical transactions, exposing wallet addresses, balances, and transaction graphs.

[b]Timeline:[/b] IBM's quantum roadmap projects 4,000+ qubit systems by 2025. Cryptographically relevant quantum computers may arrive by 2030-2035.

[b]Cost of Waiting:[/b] Every day Bitcoin, Ethereum, and other chains run on RSA/ECDSA, they accumulate quantum-vulnerable history.

[b][color=#00ff00]Q-NarwhalKnight's Advantage:[/color][/b] Born quantum-resistant. No legacy to migrate. No vulnerable history to protect. [b]Security from block zero.[/b]

